Subject: leds: register out-of-tree TI LP5812 driver
From: mihakralj <mihakralj@users.noreply.github.com>

Mono Gateway DK uses a TI LP5812 12-channel I2C LED controller for chassis
status indicators. The driver is not in mainline 6.6.y; the source tree
ships a copy under drivers/leds/lp5812/ via release/patches/kernel/sdk-sources/.

This patch:
  - adds the per-driver Kconfig + Makefile that gate compilation on
    CONFIG_LEDS_LP5812 (a bool, depends on LEDS_CLASS && I2C, selects
    LEDS_CLASS_MULTICOLOR for multi-color slot support),
  - wires the new subdirectory into drivers/leds/Kconfig and
    drivers/leds/Makefile so the kbuild walk picks it up.

CONFIG_LEDS_LP5812=y is asserted in release/ask.config so the merge_config
chain pins the driver built-in (Mono boot expects the LEDs to be operable
before fancontrol/boot-complete-notify userspace runs).

Source: based on we-are-mono/meta-mono recipes-kernel/lp5812-driver/files,
identical to vyos-ls1046a-build/data/kernel-patches/lp5812/ (commit 6a47da3b).
Migrated to the producer repo so the prebuilt linux-*.deb published as
kernel-6.6.135-askN actually carries the driver -- the consumer-side inject
became dead code when the kernel build moved out of vyos-ls1046a-build.

Signed-off-by: mihakralj <mihakralj@users.noreply.github.com>

diff --git a/drivers/leds/Kconfig b/drivers/leds/Kconfig
index 3132439f9..5ab892848 100644
--- a/drivers/leds/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/leds/Kconfig
@@ -1028,6 +1028,9 @@ source "drivers/leds/flash/Kconfig"
 comment "RGB LED drivers"
 source "drivers/leds/rgb/Kconfig"
 
+comment "Mono LED drivers"
+source "drivers/leds/lp5812/Kconfig"
+
 comment "LED Triggers"
 source "drivers/leds/trigger/Kconfig"
 
diff --git a/drivers/leds/Makefile b/drivers/leds/Makefile
index d7348e8bc..eb39eae68 100644
--- a/drivers/leds/Makefile
+++ b/drivers/leds/Makefile
@@ -124,3 +124,6 @@ obj-y					+= blink/
 
 # Simatic LED drivers
 obj-y					+= simatic/
+
+# Mono Gateway: TI LP5812 I2C LED controller (out-of-tree, sourced via sdk-sources)
+obj-$(CONFIG_LEDS_LP5812)		+= lp5812/
diff --git a/drivers/leds/lp5812/Kconfig b/drivers/leds/lp5812/Kconfig
new file mode 100644
index 000000000..fef135dd0
--- /dev/null
+++ b/drivers/leds/lp5812/Kconfig
@@ -0,0 +1,11 @@
+# SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0-only
+config LEDS_LP5812
+	bool "LED Support for TI LP5812 I2C LED controller (Mono Gateway)"
+	depends on LEDS_CLASS && I2C && OF
+	select LEDS_CLASS_MULTICOLOR
+	help
+	  This option enables support for the TI LP5812 12-channel I2C LED
+	  controller used by the Mono Gateway DK chassis status indicators.
+	  Supports per-LED PWM and multi-color slots via the kernel's
+	  multicolor LED class. Source is shipped out-of-tree under
+	  drivers/leds/lp5812/ (originally from we-are-mono/meta-mono).
diff --git a/drivers/leds/lp5812/Makefile b/drivers/leds/lp5812/Makefile
new file mode 100644
index 000000000..888a88dfc
--- /dev/null
+++ b/drivers/leds/lp5812/Makefile
@@ -0,0 +1,2 @@
+# SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0-only
+obj-$(CONFIG_LEDS_LP5812) += leds-lp5812.o
